  "prompt": "What should I put on sweet potato fries?",
  "response": "Sweet potato fries are a versatile base for all sorts of flavors! Here's a breakdown of ideas, from simple to adventurous:\n\n**Classic & Simple:**\n\n*   **Salt:** A good quality sea salt or kosher salt is always a must!\n*   **Pepper:** Freshly ground black pepper adds a nice kick.\n*   **Cinnamon Sugar:** A little bit of cinnamon and sugar is a classic pairing for sweet potato fries.\n*   **Garlic Powder:** A touch of garlic powder can add a savory element.\n*   **Chili Powder:** Adds a smoky and slightly spicy kick.\n\n**Sauces & Dips:**\n\n*   **Aioli:** Garlic aioli is a popular choice. You can buy it pre-made or make your own.\n*   **Spicy Mayo:** Combine mayonnaise with sriracha, chili garlic sauce, or your favorite hot sauce.\n*   **Chipotle Mayo:** Mix mayonnaise with chipotle peppers in adobo sauce (finely chopped) and a little adobo sauce itself.\n*   **Honey Mustard:** A classic sweet and tangy dip.\n*   **Ranch Dressing:** A comfort food favorite.\n*   **BBQ Sauce:** Especially good if you're going for a smoky flavor profile.\n*   **Avocado Crema:** Blend avocado, sour cream or Greek yogurt, lime juice, cilantro, and a pinch of salt.\n*   **Maple Syrup:** Drizzle it lightly for a truly decadent treat.\n*   **Peanut Sauce:** a savory Asian-inspired peanut sauce\n\n**Savory Toppings:**\n\n*   **Parmesan Cheese:** Grated Parmesan cheese adds a salty and nutty flavor.\n*   **Fresh Herbs:** Chopped parsley, cilantro, chives, or thyme add freshness.\n*   **Crumbled Bacon:** Because everything is better with bacon!\n*   **Pulled Pork:** Top with BBQ sauce for a complete meal.\n*   **Chili:** A hearty chili topping transforms the fries into a loaded dish.\n*   **Fried Egg:** Place a fried egg on top for a breakfast-for-dinner twist.\n*   **Feta Cheese:** Crumbled feta adds a salty and tangy flavor that complements the sweetness of the fries.\n*   **Everything Bagel Seasoning:** adds a nutty, salty, and garlicky flavor\n\n**Sweet & Spicy Combinations:**\n\n*   **Honey and Chili Flakes:** Drizzle honey and sprinkle red pepper flakes for a sweet and spicy kick.\n*   **Maple Syrup and Smoked Paprika:** A smoky and sweet combination.\n*   **Brown Sugar and Cayenne Pepper:** A caramelized sweetness with a fiery finish.\n*   **Ginger and Soy Sauce:** A more sophisticated savory-sweet option.\n\n**Tips for Topping:**\n\n*   **Apply while hot:** Toppings will adhere better to warm fries.\n*   **Don't overdo it:** Too many toppings can make the fries soggy or overwhelming.\n*   **Consider the overall meal:** Choose toppings that complement the other dishes you're serving.\n*   **Experiment!** The best way to find your favorite combination is to try different things.\n\nHave fun experimenting and enjoy your delicious sweet potato fries!\n",
